properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 4 at 3:03AM EST until January 5 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Miami FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 20 to 30 kt expected. Frequent gusts up
to 35 to 38 kt possible, highest for waters beyond 10 NM from
shore. Seas 6 to 10 feet expected, with locally higher seas
possible especially over the Gulf Stream.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Jupiter Inlet to Deerfield Beach
FL out 20 NM, Coastal waters from Deerfield Beach to Ocean
Reef FL out 20 NM and Waters from Deerfield Beach to Ocean
Reef FL from 20 to 60 NM excluding the territorial waters of
Bahamas.

* WHEN...From this evening through Sunday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.

A sudden onset of rough seas may cause hazardous conditions,
which may occur suddenly at jetties and inlets. These conditions
could catch boaters by surprise. Boaters should use caution when
entering or exiting the inlets and jetty areas.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM THIS EVENING THROUGH SUNDAY AFTERNOON
